        <mxCell id="HTBFFHoUUt1TWve2A3QG-30" value="&lt;h1 style=&quot;margin-top: 0px;&quot;&gt;Multi-GPT-2&lt;/h1&gt;&lt;div&gt;We can try to train multiple GPT-2 from scratch in a sort of encoder-decoder architecture.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;background-color: transparent; color: light-dark(rgb(0, 0, 0), rgb(255, 255, 255));&quot;&gt;Since the output size of GPT-2 can be variable, one of the GPT-2 goes through the entire movie script but &quot;window chunk&quot; by chunk and spits out an embedding vector.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;background-color: transparent; color: light-dark(rgb(0, 0, 0), rgb(255, 255, 255));&quot;&gt;After that&#39;s done the entire embedding sequence gets fed to another GPT-2 which can fit the &quot;compressed&quot; sequence into its context window and predicts the probability of Oscar nomination.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;background-color: transparent; color: light-dark(rgb(0, 0, 0), rgb(255, 255, 255));&quot;&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;background-color: transparent; color: light-dark(rgb(0, 0, 0), rgb(255, 255, 255));&quot;&gt;(this idea is likely not necessary to explore since the second GPT-2 has to be trained from scratch, which basically becomes the TransformerDecoder module in PyTorch)&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/div&gt;" style="text;html=1;whiteSpace=wrap;overflow=hidden;rounded=0;" parent="1" vertex="1">
          <mxGeometry x="1948" y="1662" width="312" height="260" as="geometry" />
        </mxCell>
