        <mxCell id="PsWw-TjkE14OrNLOrDKp-14" value="can&#39;t this also work?&lt;div&gt;decoder processes the encoded vector sequence autoregressively&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;use the last output only for the basis of classification.&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;this would be analogous to &quot;reading the entire script&quot; before reaching a decision.&lt;/div&gt;" style="rounded=0;whiteSpace=wrap;html=1;fillColor=#f8cecc;strokeColor=#b85450;align=left;verticalAlign=top;spacingLeft=8;spacing=0;spacingRight=4;" vertex="1" parent="1">
          <mxGeometry x="-1490" y="-1970" width="160" height="180" as="geometry" />
        </mxCell>
        <mxCell id="PsWw-TjkE14OrNLOrDKp-15" value="it is worth revisiting the Classification Finetuning example in Building LLMs from Scratch.&lt;div&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;as i recall, the spam classification problem was solved by:&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;token_seq =&amp;gt; GPT Decoder =&amp;gt; output_dim =&amp;gt; classification head =&amp;gt; [prob_spam, prob not]&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;So can&#39;t we use a transformer decoder instead of GPT decoder, AND somehow convert a whole screenplay into 1024 integer sequence, ending up with the same &quot;pipeline&quot;&lt;/div&gt;" style="rounded=0;whiteSpace=wrap;html=1;fillColor=#f8cecc;strokeColor=#b85450;align=left;verticalAlign=top;spacingLeft=8;spacing=0;spacingRight=4;" vertex="1" parent="1">
          <mxGeometry x="-1240" y="-1970" width="160" height="320" as="geometry" />
        </mxCell>
      </root>
    </mxGraphModel>
  </diagram>
